===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|Armenia|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|Ἀρμενία|sc=polytonic|tr=Armenia|lang=grc}} (early 5th century BC), from {{etyl|peo|en}} {{term|𐎠𐎼𐎷𐎡𐎴|sc=Xpeo|lang=peo|tr=Armina}} (late 6th century BC); see it for more. The Old Persian name is an [[exonym]]: see {{term|հայ||sc=Armn|tr=hay|lang=xcl}} for the native name. Attested in English since late 14th century.

